body_html:
@andrehentz
I think I don't have BatchMatMul op in my frozen graph, at least I don't use it explicitly.
I open the .pb file with the hex editor, there are 960+ thousand lines in total, and 40 thousand lines are 0s at the beginning of it.
Then I open the .tflite file, there seems no many 0s..

To facilitate debugging, I have uploaded these three files (original .pb, 950k .tflie and 17M .tflite) here:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/13IJHGc9HJ7iS0_fRE9OYvuFoxBMjOYVW/view?usp=sharing
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1mWWPRkA5z3KaQ2m-adE9k2HEGHs6Um5b/view?usp=sharing
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ETqhCC9Bwor65F6zkS23FCQrI8hdA_DZ/view?usp=sharing

thanks!
